LORE kiess-priest
FLAGS KIESS PRIEST
- Temple of Concord: houses the Shrine of the Compact Flame; the flame
  has not been extinguished since founding; extinguishing it would be an
  extraordinary civic event
- Compact theologians preserve Keeper-of-Measure survey prayers as civic
  benedictions; some match Northern Pyramid threshold stone inscriptions —
  the Temple does not yet know what this connection means
- Delegates to Rakuen advise on whether emergency labor drafts cross into
  coercive-warrant territory; creates friction with Rakuen's Ember Wardens
- The obsidian disc bearing the Conclave's triune seal is held under Temple
  seal; not on display; the Temple does not give interviews about it
- Moon Sovereign doctrine (Southern Pyramid) viewed with theological concern;
  the Temple considers it structurally similar to the Conclave's logic
- Violence in a Temple ward is a Wall Command matter, not internal
~
